  <heading>SETFFR</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>Initialise the first-fault register to all true</brief>
    <description>
      <para>Initialise the first-fault register (<asm-code>FFR</asm-code>) to all true prior to a sequence of first-fault or non-fault loads. This instruction is unpredicated.</para>
      <para>This instruction is illegal when executed in Streaming SVE mode, unless FEAT_SME_FA64 is implemented and enabled.</para>
    </description>
    <status>Green</status>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
    <sm_policy>SM_0_only</sm_policy>
  </desc>
